    {
      "id": "29bc6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Chinese major offers a very extensive array of courses in Chinese language, premodern and modern literature, linguistics, religion, archaeology, and film. Students are required to achieve advanced levels of proficiency in modern spoken and written Chinese, while also acquiring basic knowledge of premodern texts. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One year of college level declared Asian language OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared Asian language. Completion of two years of college level declared Asian language courses are STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// alc.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Chinese major offers a very extensive array of courses in Chinese language, premodern and modern literature, linguistics, religion, archaeology, and film. Students are required to achieve advanced levels of proficiency in modern spoken and written Chinese, while also acquiring basic knowledge of premodern texts.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level declared Asian language OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was the declared Asian language.</li></ul><p>Completion of two years of college level declared Asian language courses are <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>.</p><p>A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding preparation for this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.alc.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">alc.ucla.edu</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
